  <h1>About Book Management System</h1>

  <!-- Project description section -->
  <div class="about-section">
    <h2>Project Overview</h2>
    <p>
      This Book Management System is an academic project developed to
      demonstrate proficiency in web development using Node.js, Express,
      Handlebars templating, and SQLite3 database management.
    </p>
    <p>
      The system allows users to browse a collection of books, view detailed
      information about each book including author and genre details, and
      perform CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete) on the book
      database with proper authentication.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Technical features section -->
  <div class="about-section">
    <h2>Technical Features</h2>
    <ul class="feature-list">
      <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Node.js with Express framework</li>
      <li><strong>Template Engine:</strong>
        Handlebars (.hbs) for server-side rendering</li>
      <li><strong>Database:</strong>
        SQLite3 with relational tables (Books, Authors, Genres)</li>
      <li><strong>Authentication:</strong>
        Secure login system with bcrypt password hashing</li>
      <li><strong>Security:</strong>
        SQL injection prevention using parameterized queries</li>
      <li><strong>Pagination:</strong>
        Book list with 3 items per page navigation</li>
      <li><strong>CRUD Operations:</strong>
        Full create, read, update, and delete functionality</li>
      <li><strong>Database Joins:</strong>
        INNER JOIN queries combining multiple tables</li>
      <li><strong>Responsive Design:</strong>
        Clean UI using Flexbox and CSS Grid</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Database structure section -->
  <div class="about-section">
    <h2>Database Structure</h2>
    <p>The system uses three interconnected tables:</p>
    <ul class="feature-list">
      <li><strong>Authors:</strong>
        Stores author information (name, birth year, country)</li>
      <li><strong>Genres:</strong> Stores book genres and descriptions</li>
      <li><strong>Books:</strong>
        Stores book details with foreign keys to authors and genres</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The database contains over 9 records distributed across these tables, with
      proper relationships established through foreign key constraints.
    </p>
  </div>

